14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3419.1 of Title 70, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. As used in this section, the term "financial institution"
19 means banks, savings banks, savings and loan associations, and
20 credit unions in this state whose deposits are insured by the
21 Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, the National Credit Union
22 Administration or any successor institutions. Such financial
23 institution shall be in good standing, conduct regular banking
24 business, and shall collect such drafts, bills of exchange, and
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3557 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 chec ks as may be deposited by the local entity or division in the
2 regular course of business. Such financial institution shall pay
3 all checks and drafts legally authorized and duly drawn on the funds
4 deposited.
5 B. The Oklahoma Agricultural Extension Division shall not,
6 directly or as a condition of providing Oklahoma Agricultural
7 Extension Division services or providing access to Oklahoma
8 Agricultural Experiment Station programming, require funding
9 generated at the local county level, as described by subsection C of
10 this section, to be:
11 1. Centralized at the Division or Station; or
12 2. Directed or expended outside the county in which the funding
13 was generated.
14 C. Each local entity or division of the county extension
15 service system, including any unincorporated association, nonprofit
16 entity or other legal entity assisting with fundraising activities
17 for the benefit of a local entity or division of the county
18 extension service system which receives an allocation of state funds
19 through the Oklahoma Agricultural Extension Division is authorized
20 to select a financial institution within the State of Oklahoma and
21 establish one or more accounts at the same for funds generated,
22 raised, or collected at the local county level to pay expenses
23 related to the services delivered through the county extension
24 service system.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3557 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 D. No state appropriated or federal funds shall be deposited in
2 any account owned or controlled by a local entity or division of the
3 county extension service system.
4 E. Accounts established under subsection C of this section are
5 authorized to retain interest, and the interest income shall not be
6 used for any purpose inconsistent with the terms of the account as
7 provided in the agreement with the applicable financial institution.
8 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND WILDLIFE
